version_description: To best explain this, you toggle play the notes on the E/ and A/ runs. (E/B = E note b note)in a back and forth style. It is Roger's base playing style on an acoustic guitar embellished by Dave's overlaying of the higher notes. I have done this live and it always gets great response. The only reason I didn't make it novice is the tricky pluck timing. for visual reference https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2DAdWcsM7Po.
Some additional subtler suggestions for the C and D chords.
Same as the other version, I just added the missing lyrics and did some formatting...
The other chord versions do not include the alternating bass notes.
Better chords, timing, section headings, more compact format, consistent with lesson: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_168COZBD-c.
Complete version, along with tab accompaniment.
